                {
                    "id": "8e9d9c591f994af1a5fc2",
                    "stepText": "At equilibrium, the block\u2019s kinetic energy is equal to the initial spring energy minus the work done against friction, giving approximately $!$3.31$!$ J. Now, identify the correct energy balance equation for the motion beyond equilibrium where this remaining kinetic energy is used both to store additional spring energy and to do work against friction as the block moves an extra distance $!$x$!$. Which option best represents this energy balance?",
